---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TravelAffiliateBox from '../components/TravelAffiliateBox.astro';
const PUB_DATE = '2026-05-04';
const travelDestinations = [
  {
    name: 'Shimoda',
    description: 'A key place for Perry, treaty-port history, and the opening of Japan.',
    placeHref: 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Shimoda%20Japan%20Perry%20Road',
    stayHref: 'https://www.booking.com/searchresults.html?ss=Shimoda%2C%20Shizuoka%2C%20Japan',
  },
  {
    name: 'Kyoto Bakumatsu sites',
    description: 'The strongest base for Shinsengumi, imperial court politics, and late Tokugawa conflict.',
    placeHref: 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Kyoto%20Shinsengumi%20Mibu-dera',
    stayHref: 'https://www.booking.com/searchresults.html?ss=Kyoto%2C%20Japan',
  },
  {
    name: 'Kagoshima',
    description: 'A useful route into Satsuma, Saigō Takamori, and the forces that reshaped Meiji Japan.',
    placeHref: 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Saigo%20Takamori%20Kagoshima',
    stayHref: 'https://www.booking.com/searchresults.html?ss=Kagoshima%2C%20Japan',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Bakumatsu: The End of the Samurai Era"
  description="A pillar guide to Bakumatsu (1853–1868) — Japan's collision with the West, the fall of the Tokugawa shogunate, and the men who chose between worlds."
  type="article"
>
  <ArticleSchema
    slot="head"
    headline="Bakumatsu: The End of the Samurai Era"
    description="A pillar guide to Bakumatsu (1853–1868) — Japan's collision with the West, the fall of the Tokugawa shogunate, and the men who chose between worlds."
    datePublished={PUB_DATE}
  />

  <h1>Bakumatsu: The End of the Samurai Era</h1>
  <p>
    Bakumatsu — literally "the end of the curtain" — names the fifteen years
    between Commodore Perry's black ships (1853) and the Meiji Restoration
    (1868). It is the period in which Japan stopped being one thing and
    started being another.
  </p>

  <h2>Articles in this series</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Why Did Japan Close Its Borders for 250 Years?</li>
    <li>Why Sakamoto Ryōma Is Still Japan's Hero</li>
    <li>The Black Ships: What Perry Did and What Japan Did Next</li>
  </ul>

  <TravelAffiliateBox
    destinations={travelDestinations}
    title="Travel links for Bakumatsu readers"
    intro="For readers planning a history-focused trip, these places connect the late shogunate with treaty ports, Kyoto conflict, and Satsuma history."
  />
</BaseLayout>
